						               													<description>This is a tie-in to the 2005 Charlie and the Chocolate Factory movie.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each Squomino has an Oompa-Loompa in a colored uniform on each of its four sides. Players link pairs of matching Oompa-Loompas by placing the Squominos in a spiral shape.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players start with 7 Squominos. If they cannot play a Squomino on their turn, they pick one up from the pool. The winner is the first to run out of Squominos.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Therefore the choice is which Squomino to use, not where.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 58 Squominos, including 3 wild cards (which can match anything). Oompa-Loompas are in just four colors: green, red, yellow and blue.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This simplicity makes the game suitable for Ages 3 and up.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
